On 27 Mar 1999, Ben Pfaff wrote:
> "christophe leroy" <christophe.leroy5@capway.com> writes:
> 
>    Can someone tell me where I can find docs to write a frame buffer 
>    driver ?
> 
> AFAIK there aren't any real docs beyond those in Documentation/fb.
> When I was writing a VGA 16-color framebuffer driver I found the
> source code to other framebuffer drivers for Linux to be the best
> reference.
I used the TGA driver source when I was writing a graphics-mode VGA
console driver a while back. It's probably your best bet since the TGA is
a really simple framebuffer board.
